<h2 class="page-title span-24">Case Study: Aeroplan</h2>

<div class="header span-24">
  <div class="span-19 last">
    <h1>
      <span class="dark-green">Aeroplan needed a solid platform</span>
      for their Request Tracker application.
    </h1>
    <img src="http://static.gossamer-threads.com/r3/images/logos/logo-aeroplan-120x54.png" width="120" height="54" alt="Aeroplan logo" />
  </div>
</div><!-- end .header -->

<div class="span-15 append-1 content-text"><!-- main-col -->
  <h2>Challenge</h2>
  <p>
    Having decided that Request Tracker was the right solution to
    build their support ticketing system on, Aeroplan needed a hosting company
    with the in-depth skills and experience required to run this complex
    application in a sound and secure environment. Two existing RT
    installations (one for support calls and one for internal office data) and
    their large databases needed to be migrated intact to the new platform
    without any interruption to their normal workflow.
  </p>

  <h2>Solution</h2>
  <p>
    Based on our <a href="/hosting/request-tracker.html">managed request
      tracker hosting platform</a>, Gossamer developed a complex hosting
    configuration to meet the demand and performance levels required by
    Aeroplan. Existing configurations were mirrored and a redundant hardware
    and server platform were implemented and tested within a short timeframe.
    Three dry runs of the migration of the two RT instances were completed,
    transferring the data to the new servers without any downtime. These dry
    runs gave Gossamer Host and Aeroplan’s sysadmins a precise estimate of
    the time and work required for the live migration.
  </p>

  <h2>Results</h2>
  <p>
    The migration was completed on schedule with no data loss and no user-side
    downtime. In addition to RT applications, multiple custom scripts developed
    by Gossamer Threads run in a smooth and stable fashion on the new platform.
    Aeroplan’s support system is currently the largest Request Tracker
    install, handling over 6,000 tickets per day. After the migration, wait
    times for support requests dropped dramatically from weeks to hours.
  </p>

  <p class="more"><a href="/hosting/request-tracker.html">More about our managed Request Tracker hosting&nbsp;<span>&raquo;</span></a></p>

